r for me than a 2k/800.<br><br>Thoughts?<br><br><br><br>Edit: Plus, it's always nice to have a goal in mind to keep you steady... <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uwyrdlan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wyrdlan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0> at: 9/18/02 6:32:12 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usurlok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Surlok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 77<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/18/02 8:13:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3923.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ac.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Equiptment Check: Trading HP for AC</span><hr size=1> It will be difficult for you to get your AC much higher now simply because you will recieve no defensive skill ups.So for now while you may only get 800 ac from the gear you have that number will start to rise quickly when you reach 51 and beyond...<br><br>Your gear is good..don't get stuck thinking you need to have the best gear unless you are going to be the Main Tank in your guild when you reach your lower 50's then your best bet is to just level away and enjoy the game...because until the high 50's the only big difference 900 ac to 1100 ac is that oyu may be able to solo mobs..once you get to 46 you will start raiding planes and gear will come..Take your time now and level ...and remeber to have fun.. <p>myrmidon \MUR-muh-don; -dun\, noun:1. A loyal follower, especially one who executes orders without question, protest, or pity. - <a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=282318>Surlok Soulbain</a> - Officer of<a href=http://www.spod